        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued August 28 at 3:37PM EDT until August 29 at 10:00AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerous swimming conditions are expected due to high
waves of 3 to 7 feet and rip currents.

* WHERE...Huron, Sanilac and St. Clair Counties.

* WHEN...From 2 PM EDT this afternoon through Friday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.</instruction>
